sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Phone (offline edit)
    participant ADB as Phone's local SQLite
    participant Srv as Sync API (MacBook)
    participant SDB as Server DB
    participant BDB as Desktop's local SQLite
    participant B as Desktop

    Note over A,ADB: No connection needed to edit
    A->>ADB: create/edit item
    ADB-->>A: UI updates instantly

    Note over A,Srv: Phone reconnects (Tailscale reachable)
    A->>Srv: POST /push (changes since last sync)
    Srv->>SDB: compare updated_at per row, apply last-write-wins
    SDB-->>Srv: ack

    Note over B,Srv: Desktop reconnects independently, any time later
    B->>Srv: GET /pull?since=<desktop's last sync time>
    Srv->>SDB: fetch rows changed since then
    SDB-->>Srv: changed rows
    Srv-->>B: changed rows
    B->>BDB: apply incoming changes
    BDB-->>B: UI updates automatically, no manual refresh
